<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="295" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1126,1694]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1163,1189]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Glasby, C. J. &amp; Hutchings, P. A." box="[325,645,1163,1189]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" pagination="29 - 52" refId="ref11449" refString="Glasby, C. J. &amp; Hutchings, P. A. (2010) A new species of Marphysa Quatrefages, 1865 (Polychaeta: Eunicida: Eunicidae) from northern Australia and a review of similar forms from the tropical Indo-west Pacific. Zootaxa, 2352, 29 - 52." type="journal article" year="2010">Glasby &amp; Hutchings (2010)</bibRefCitation>
provide a description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Southern" authorityYear="1921" box="[940,1072,1163,1189]" class="Polychaeta" family="Eunicidae" genus="Marphysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Eunicida" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="gravelyi">
<emphasis box="[940,1072,1163,1189]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">M. gravelyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the 
<typeStatus box="[1237,1333,1163,1189]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">paratype</typeStatus>
(BMNH 1938.5.7.55) and the type description in their 
<tableCitation box="[683,770,1199,1225]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="14.[151,239,537,563]" captionText="TABLE 3. Diagnostic characters for species of the Mossambica- and Teretiuscula-groups reported from the coasts of India and the broader Indian Ocean" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">Table 3</tableCitation>
. The important diagnostic characters are: median antenna slightly longer than outer pair with palps similar in length to outer antenna; branchiae from segments 22–52 and continuing almost to pygidium with a maximum of 5–9 filaments and much longer than dorsal cirri; pectinate chaetae from mid-body onwards (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Southern, R." box="[533,709,1307,1333]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" pagination="563 - 659" refId="ref12925" refString="Southern, R. (1921) Polychaeta of the Chilka Lake and also of fresh and brackish waters in other parts of India. Memoirs of the Indian Museum, 5, 563 - 659." type="journal article" year="1921">Southern, 1921</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 13K, plate XXV); compound spinigers present after about chaetiger 100; bidentate subacicular hooks present from chaetiger 26 to 35 and two per chaetiger.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="295" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1126,1694]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,1379,1405]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">Ecology</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Southern, R." box="[309,485,1379,1405]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" pagination="563 - 659" refId="ref12925" refString="Southern, R. (1921) Polychaeta of the Chilka Lake and also of fresh and brackish waters in other parts of India. Memoirs of the Indian Museum, 5, 563 - 659." type="journal article" year="1921">Southern (1921</bibRefCitation>
, page 620) records that Annandale (in litt.) mentions an eunicid worm that produces large balloon-like masses of gelatinous spawn anchored to the mud by a tubiculous structure.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1126,1694]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3008332307" country="Sri Lanka" county="This" location="Southern" municipality="No" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" specimenCount="1">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:8F338796FFE8FFECFF1D129C173CEB91:0245605BFFE8FFECFF4D14F01735E8CA" box="[199,300,1451,1477]" country="Sri Lanka" county="This" municipality="No" name="Southern" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">Southern</location>
also suggests that this may be the same species as 
<bibRefCitation author="Borradaile, L. A." box="[866,1065,1451,1477]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" pagination="714 - 720" refId="ref10734" refString="Borradaile, L. A. (1901) On the spawn and young of a polychaete worm of the genus Marphysa. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1901, 714 - 720, pl. 39. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1902. tb 08198. x" type="journal article" year="1901">Borradaile (1901)</bibRefCitation>
reported from a lagoon at 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:8F338796FFE8FFECFF1D129C173CEB91:0245605BFFE8FFECFADB14F01381E8CA" box="[1361,1432,1451,1477]" country="Sri Lanka" county="This" municipality="No" name="Jaffna" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">Jaffna</location>
, on the northern coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[423,532,1487,1513]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
which also produces eggs in jelly cocoon attached to the bottom by a short stalk, and described the early development. 
<collectingMunicipality box="[571,605,1523,1549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">No</collectingMunicipality>
material was deposited though. 
<collectingCounty box="[962,1012,1523,1549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">This</collectingCounty>
record is far closer to the 
<typeStatus box="[1298,1346,1523,1549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hutchings &amp; Lavesque &amp; Priscilla &amp; Daffe &amp; Malathi &amp; Glasby, 2020" authorityName="Hutchings &amp; Lavesque &amp; Priscilla &amp; Daffe &amp; Malathi &amp; Glasby" authorityYear="2020" box="[182,311,1559,1585]" class="Polychaeta" family="Eunicidae" genus="Marphysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Eunicida" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="madrasi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[182,311,1559,1585]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">M. madrasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[318,380,1559,1585]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[318,380,1559,1585]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but without voucher material we cannot confirm the possible conspecificity
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="295" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1126,1694]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1594,1620]" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">Distribution.</emphasis>
Chilka Lake, 
<collectingCountry box="[515,575,1595,1621]" name="India" pageId="10" pageNumber="295">India</collectingCountry>
, 19°28’ and 
<geoCoordinate box="[719,824,1594,1621]" degrees="19" direction="north" minutes="54" orientation="latitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" precision="925" value="19.9">19°54’ N</geoCoordinate>
. and 85°6’ and 
<geoCoordinate box="[1003,1105,1594,1621]" degrees="85" direction="east" minutes="35" orientation="longitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" precision="925" value="85.583336">85°35’ E</geoCoordinate>
. (the current co-ordinates for the lake are 
<geoCoordinate box="[289,447,1630,1657]" degrees="19" direction="north" minutes="28" orientation="latitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" precision="1" seconds="21.5" value="19.47264">19°28’21.5”N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[455,610,1630,1657]" degrees="85" direction="east" minutes="07" orientation="longitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" precision="1" seconds="32.4" value="85.12567">85°07’32.4”E</geoCoordinate>
and 
<geoCoordinate box="[665,809,1630,1657]" degrees="9" direction="north" minutes="52" orientation="latitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" precision="1" seconds="23.9" value="9.873305">9°52’23.9”N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[817,974,1630,1657]" degrees="85" direction="east" minutes="33" orientation="longitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="295" precision="1" seconds="03.2" value="85.550896">85°33’03.2”E</geoCoordinate>
, as the lake has shrunk since the original description).
</paragraph>
